Simulate Dose-Response Data from a Log-Linear Model

Source: R/simulate_loglinear.R
simulate_loglinear.Rd

Simulates from a log-linear dose-response model: $$pred = e0 + delta * log(dose + log_shift)$$

simulate_loglinear(
  dose_levels,
  n_per_dose,
  e0,
  delta,
  log_shift = 1,
  sigma,
  dist = "normal",
  df = 3,
  seed = NULL
)

Arguments

dose_levels

Numeric vector of dose levels.

n_per_dose

Either a single integer (equal sample size per dose) or a vector matching `dose_levels`.

e0

Baseline effect. Can be a scalar or a vector.

delta

Slope of the log-linear relationship.

log_shift

Value added inside the log to avoid log(0). Default is 1.

sigma

Standard deviation for residual error.

dist

Residual error distribution: `"normal"` (default), `"lognormal"`, `"uniform"`, `"t"`, or `"gamma"`.

df

Degrees of freedom for t-distribution.

seed

Optional seed for reproducibility.

Value

Data frame with columns: `id`, `dose`, `pred`, `ipred`, `scenario`.

Details

All combinations of `e0`, `delta`, and `log_shift` will be simulated.

Examples

simulate_loglinear(
  dose_levels = c(0, 1, 5, 10),
  n_per_dose = 10,
  e0 = c(0, 0.1), delta = c(1.5, 1.8), log_shift = c(0.5, 1),
  sigma = 0.2,
  dist = "normal",
  seed = 100
)
